{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T13:28:28.407Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Input vs Output Budget: Managing Your Context Window"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The context window is a shared budget where input tokens (your prompts, conversation history, files, tool outputs) and output tokens (Claude's responses) both count toward the same 200k–1M token limit, but they cost differently—output tokens are 4–5× more expensive per token than input tokens across all Claude models"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"The Shared Budget Architecture"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│              CONTEXT WINDOW BUDGET                       │\n│                                                           │\n│  Input Tokens     +     Output Tokens     =    LIMIT    │\n│  (your prompts)         (Claude's reply)                │\n│  + files                  + thinking tokens             │\n│  + tool outputs                                                │\n│  + conversation history   (max_tokens)                   │\n│                                                           │\n│  0      50k     100k     150k     200k     ...   1M    │\n│  └───────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n│                    ↑                                      │\n│              FIXED CAPACITY                               │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key insight"},{"type":"text","text":": Your context window is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"not"},{"type":"text","text":" separate pools for input and output—